===Etymology 1===
[[Image:Biber-drawing.jpg|thumb|Beavers]]
{{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|beofor|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|ƀeƀruz|lang=en}} (compare Dutch {{term|bever|lang=nl}}, German {{term|Biber|lang=de}}, {{etyl|sv|-}} {{term|bäver}}), from {{proto|Indo-European|bhébhrus}} 'beaver' (compare {{etyl|cy|-}} {{term|befer}}, [[Latin]] ''fiber'', {{etyl|lt|-}} {{term|bẽbras|lang=lt}}, [[Russian]] ''bobr'', {{etyl|ae|-}} ''bawra, bawri'', [[Sanskrit]] ''babhrú'' 'mongoose; reddish-brown'), from *''bhreu-'' 'shining, brown'. Related to [[brown]] and [[bear]].

====Noun====
{{en-noun|pl2=beaver}}

# An [[aquatic]] [[mammal]] of the genus ''[[Castor]]'', having a wide, flat tail and webbed feet.
# A tall hat, originally made from beaver fur, worn by men in the 1800s.
# {{context|coarse|slang}} The [[pubic hair]] and/or [[vulva]] of a woman.

